Lexington is where Tim Williams, owner and broker-in-charge at 803 Realty , grew up. 803 Realty offers a stress-free approach to buying and selling real estate through partnerships with industry leaders throughout the purchasing or selling process. These partnerships and connections allow clients to feel at ease and know that every step of the process is being held with the utmost care and urgency. The agency has also partnered with a property management company that allows for their clients to have a one stop approach to real estate. 803 Realty rebranded in June of 2020, after first opening its doors as Williams Real Estate Group in January 2016 as a full service residential real estate company. Tim and the other 42 agents pride themselves on their VIP client level customer service. They are selling homes 25 days faster than the Midlands average and operate as a one stop shop for both real estate sales and rentals. Tim is continually expanding to service communities throughout the 803 area code. He recently announced the expansion of their sales force to the Aiken/North Augusta market. The agency continues to focus on finding new ways to serve the community by joining multiple charitable foundations and business leaders that work to beautify the town and encourage growth and diversity. Everyday, Tim gets to help individuals and families with one of the largest purchases of their life, real estate. Not only that, but he also gets to mentor agents who work with 803 Realty and learn new ways to serve the community and build the business. Tim is grateful how his work in this service industry has touched his life. He shared that life is a beautiful thing that we must all be grateful for and that success should be defined by the individual, not a company or corporation. "I feel as though in this industry and in any 'luxury industry' there is too much pressure on agents to work towards driving a certain car or making a certain amount of money," he said. "We all have different levels of comfort when it comes to living and different things we are working toward. I feel as though it's important as a company that we promote that individuality because that's what makes this community thrive and great". 803 Realty will always remain locally owned and operated, putting their clients and community first. Visit 803 Realty at 5599 Sunset Boulevard or at www.803realtylexington.com . Tim and his wife Cidney, are quite involved in Lexington, from helping out at the schools their four children attend to taking part in city beautification projects. They also love Lake Murray - the jewel of South Carolina. " I love time with my family and vacationing", Tim adds. "They are the center of my world."

Thank you for taking the time to read about me! I am truly fortunate to be one of those people that love what I do and where I get to do it! I think we are very fortunate to live in Northeastern Wisconsin. Wonderful communities, four seasons, neighbors who still know each other's names…Happy Valley! As an agent, I pride myself on a strong work ethic, high degree of integrity and thorough understanding of the real estate market in the Fox Valley and surrounding areas. I believe these traits set me apart from many agents. I've also won some pretty prestigious awards - they're neat, but wouldn't be possible if I wasn't focused 100% on meeting the needs of my Buyers and Sellers. Selling your Home? Data-driven pricing opinions. Any agent can tell you what you want to hear. I'll tell you what the market is indicating and how to place your home in the best position to get the best price possible. Marketing. Top of the line marketing including: Immediate exposure on MLS Social media exposure Presence on over 350 websites (Zillow, Trulia, Realtor.com, HomeFinder, etc) On-line virtual tour Open houses Print media Communication. You will hear from me regularly; within 24-hours of a showing and the same day of open houses. Have a question in between - call me! You work with me. I have a wonderful support staff that shuffles the paperwork and allows me to be available to you when you need me. Buying a Home? Solid understanding of home construction. This allows me to educate and assist buyers as they compare and contrast the homes they are viewing. Not all homes are constructed the same, I will explain the difference. Strong financial background. This aids in my working with savvy investors, first-time buyers and individuals who have purchased a home in the past. Born and raised in the Fox Valley - I know the area, the school districts, the local events, the best place for a wonderful Friday night fish dinner - just ask me! Welcome to the remarkable world of Alaskan real estate, where every transaction is as unique as our breathtaking landscapes. I'm Natalia, your dedicated Realtor with an unwavering passion for this remarkable state. Since 2001, Alaska has been my home, my heart, and my playground. I'm excited to share my journey with you and offer my expertise in helping you navigate the Alaskan real estate market. Rooted in the Last Frontier I put down roots in Alaska when I arrived in 2001 to pursue my education at Alaska Pacific University. Little did I know, I would fall head over heels for this incredible state, making it my permanent home after college. My years in Alaska have been marked by adventure, exploration, and a deep appreciation for the outdoors. Living Life on the Edge Alaska's rugged terrain and untamed wilderness have been my constant companions. I've hiked and scaled mountains all over the state, ventured onto glaciers, embraced the thrill of ice climbing, and carved my way through the backcountry with skis strapped to my feet. The Alaskan wilderness isn't just my playground; it's my sanctuary. Fishing and Guiding on the Kenai River My summers were dedicated to the Kenai River, where I cast my line and reeled in unforgettable memories. After college, I transitioned into guiding, fulfilling my clients' dreams of catching world-renowned trout and salmon in the pristine waters of the Kenai River. This experience instilled in me the importance of fulfilling dreams and making connections, a lesson that transcends my real estate career. Scaling New Heights for a Cause In a testament to my dedication to giving back, I climbed the tallest mountain in Europe, Mount Elbrus, in 2014 as part of a fundraiser to raise money for Easter seals. This experience reinforced my belief in the power of community and the impact we can make when we come together for a meaningful cause. Real Estate: A Path to Financial Freedom My journey in real estate began with a desire to secure passive income for my family. I knew that by helping others find their dream homes and investment properties, I could build a more secure future for my loved ones. My commitment to my clients and my drive to create financial stability have been my driving forces in this industry. Recognitions and Awards In 2022, I was honored to receive the Realtor of the Year award for the Kenai Peninsula, a testament to my dedication to the local community and the real estate profession. I take immense pride in consistently achieving excellence for the last 7 years, earning accolades like the Centurion and the President's Producer Awards from Century 21 for my commitment to providing outstanding service. "Your Property, My Priority" My motto, "Your property, my priority," encapsulates the essence of my approach to real estate. Your dreams, your investments, and your future are what matter most to me. I'll go the extra mile to ensure that your real estate journey is smooth, successful, and tailored to your unique needs. Whether you're looking to buy, sell, or invest in Alaskan real estate, I'm here to be your guide, advocate, and trusted partner. The Alaskan real estate market is as diverse and exciting as the Alaskan wilderness itself. Let's embark on this journey together, turning your real estate dreams into a reality. Get in touch with me today, and let's make your Alaskan dreams come true. ~Natalia
